An Act establishing a special commission on a statewide long-term services and supports benefit
program.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. There shall be a special commission to study and make recommendations
2 to establish a statewide long-term services and supports benefit program in the commonwealth.
3 The commission shall study and report on: (i) whether and how a long-term serves and supports
4 benefit program could be included as a benefit in the state disability insurance program structure;
5 (ii) allowances for enrollment in the program of working adults who would make premium
6 contributions either directly or through payroll deductions through their employer; (iii) requiring
7 a mandatory enrollment; (iv) giving adults the opportunity to plan for future long-term services
8 and supports needs by providing a basic insurance benefit to those who meet requirements and
9 have developed functional or equivalent cognitive limitations; (v) helping individuals with
10 functional or cognitive limitations remain in their communities by purchasing nonmedical
11 services and supports, including but not limited to personal care, homemaker, meal delivery and
12 case management services; (vi) helping offset the costs incurred by adults with chronic and
13 disabling conditions both for a defined period or until death.
