14 SECTION 2 . The commission shall consist of the following 27 members: the secretary
15 of health and human services or their designee, who shall serve as chair; the secretary of aging
16 and independence or their designee; the commissioner of insurance or their designee; the
17 assistant secretary for MassHealth or their designee; the chairs of the joint committee on aging
18 and independence or their designees; the chairs of the joint committee on financial services or
19 their designees; and 19 persons to be appointed by the governor: 1 of whom shall be a
20 representative of the Home Care Aide Council, 1 of whom shall be a representative of the Home
21 Care Alliance of Massachusetts, Inc., 1 of whom shall be a representative of Massachusetts
22 Aging Access Association, Inc,, 1 of whom shall be a representative of the Massachusetts Senior
23 Care Association, Inc., 1 of whom shall be a representative of LeadingAge Massachusetts, Inc., 1
24 of whom shall be a representative of the Massachusetts Assisted Living Association, Inc., 1 of
25 whom shall be a representative of AARP Massachusetts, 1 of whom shall be a representative of
26 Local 1199 Service Employee International Union, 1 of whom shall be a representative of the
27 Massachusetts Academy of Elder Law Attorneys, 1 of whom shall be a representative of
28 Massachusetts Senior Action Council, Inc , 1 of whom shall be a representative of Blue Cross
29 Blue Shield of Massachusetts Foundation, Inc., 1 of whom shall be a representative of the
30 National Association of Insurance and Financial Advisors of Massachusetts, 1 of whom shall be
31 a representative of Life Insurance Association of Massachusetts, Inc ,, 1 of whom shall be a
32 representative of the Massachusetts Business Roundtable, Inc , 1 of whom shall be a
33 representative of a long-term care insurance provider; 1 of whom shall be an actuary with
34 experience in long-term care insurance, 1 of whom shall be an expert on long-term care and
