36 SECTION 3 . The commission shall review the independent actuarial study of financial
37 options for modeling public, private and public-private hybrid long-term care services and
38 supports authorized in item 4000-0300 of Chapter 18 of the Acts of 2024 and conducted by
39 Milliman, Inc.; and provided further shall utilize the findings of said actuarial study to make
40 recommendations on the following: (i) how a statewide long-term services and supports benefit
41 program could be designed and implemented to expand the options for people who are interested
42 in insuring themselves against the risk of costs associated with functional or cognitive disability,
43 and require long-term services and supports; (ii) options for the design of the program, including
44 eligibility, enrollment, benefits, financing, administration, and alignment with the MassHealth
45 program and other publicly funded resources, including but not limited to the home care program
46 established in Section 4 of Chapter 19A; provided, however, that the commission shall
47 recommend a program that ensures, to the furthest extent possible, adequate funding for publicly
48 funded programs (iii) how benefits under the program would be coordinated with existing private
49 health care coverage benefits; (iv) the demands on the long-term care workforce as the need for
50 long-term services and supports in Massachusetts grows, and how the long-term care workforce
51 can be prepared to meet those demands; (v) the viability of a joint public and private system to
52 make long-term services and supports accessible to as many individuals within Massachusetts as
53 possible.
54 SECTION 4. The commission shall submit a report containing its findings and
55 recommendations, including drafts of proposed legislation to carry out its recommendations, by
56 filing the same with the clerks of the senate and house of representatives, the house and senate
57 committees on ways and means, the joint committee on aging and independence and the joint
58 committee on financial services no later than two years after the effective date of this act.
